##Late at night, I was waiting for an ambulance in Wuhan

Micro signal

Function description, we are with you in this battle

Without a bed, the suspected patient's life is being consumed. There's no diagnosis, no escape, no patient, no desperate family.

By Deng Zhiying

And Ginger contact since, my daily routine has also become three o'clock in the morning to sleep, with her waiting for the ambulance.

Ginger's grandfather, eighty-seven, is highly suspected of having a severe case of new crown pneumonia. She and her mother, who was in her late 20s, were left alone. After the traffic control, no one has a car, to take grandpa to the hospital for injections, they can only rely on the early morning shot 110,120 chance.

Of the conversation with Ginger

Here's what Ginger says:

I'm a 32-year-old female, single, and an auxiliary officer in the traffic police force. My grandfather is eighty-seven and is seriously ill.

Our Day started at 10:00 at night, calling 110 and 120, taking GRANDPA to the hospital for a shot.

We dare not go to the hospital during the day.

When GRANDPA first came to the hospital, he waited in line for the doctor for five or six hours. Another two hours in line for a CT. . We had to wheel him home, carry him upstairs. I don't sleep when I come back. I can't sleep. I can't breathe.

His illness is already very serious, we dare not again grind like this, be afraid of disease do not look at, the person gives grind away. In the early morning to the hospital line injection, people will be less, just wait three or four hours, GRANDPA can suffer less.

But calling 110 and 120 doesn't always get you a ride.

People come when they want, they don't come when they don't, and they're scared. Waiting for the car, there is no stretcher, I and his mother himself back grandpa down the stairs, and then use a wheelchair to push to the hospital, walk for an hour.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Down the stairs

The policeman who answered the phone the day before yesterday was very good. He was still willing to take us to the hospital at two o'clock in the morning, but we couldn't let others wait to take us back. Honestly, who doesn't freak out about this kind of thing?

After the injection in the early morning, we wheeled GRANDPA home and carried him upstairs. When he had rested, mother would take a nap. My mother was squinting so I could close my eyes for a while.

Let's hope we're lucky enough to wait for 110 and 120. I hope GRANDPA can make it one more day before he gets a bed.

GRANDPA's fate is too bad.

He joined the army at the age of 16 and went to Harbin to study military medicine, preparing to resist US aid to Korea on the battlefield. Before graduation, the war was over. He has been a medical officer in the army for nearly 30 years and is a veteran of the demobilization profession. Transferred to a local factory in'76. They were laid off when the factory collapsed a few years ago.

GRANDPA has Alzheimer's and has been living in a nursing home in the neighborhood. He was so well before he caught a cold that he couldn't have been eighty-seven, and everyone thought he was only seventy.

The South China Seafood Market was only 1 km from my home, and I didn't care at all.

At the time, the government said there was an outbreak in southern China and shut down the south China seafood market, without mentioning the severity of the outbreak. Our community is so close to South China, the day before the city closure, we have not yet to wear the consciousness of masks.

Before the 20th, everyone was happy to buy New Year's Eve, because the government had been saying that there was no sign of human to human transmission, and it was quite certain that it probably would not.

Online comments under the help

At first we thought it was just a common cold and fever. We didn't dare to go to the hospital. Later, repeated fever, lasting seven or eight days are not back down, day by day more serious, and finally began to breathe fast.

We have no choice but to go to the hospital. The doctor looked at the result and said it was highly doubtful. Without the box to make a definite diagnosis, we could not be admitted without a definite diagnosis. He gave us a list to come to the hospital every day for injections.

He only had my mother, and my mother only had me. My mother and father divorced when I was very young, and now we are the only three in the family.

If we don't get a car, if we don't get a man, I'm GonNa have to carry it.

Now GRANDPA lives in the back room, and my mother and I live in the living room. I keep arguing with my mother, telling her not to go up to the house. It's contagious. She wouldn't listen, and kept going up to the room to take care of her grandfather, bringing him water, food, and scrubbing, to see if he smoked too much.

She said, "that's my dad, " but she's my mom, too.

Home-made protection

I was afraid if GRANDPA left and she left, then I'd have to leave.

I called a different hospital every day, hoping to be quarantined, but there were no beds anywhere. I had to stay home and get shots.

Honestly, when it first happened, I didn't feel anything. Slowly I felt angry. And now that my family has it, and maybe I have it, I'm not angry anymore, I'm just scared and broken.

I don't want to go out. I want to stay home. But if we don't go out, who's GonNa Take Grandpa to get his shot?

I don't know how much longer GRANDPA's GonNa last, and I don't know what we're GonNa do if he dies at home. All I need is an isolation bed. It's an admission. It's help. It's the three of us.

Call the hospital, call the helpline, call 110,120, send the help post, I have tried, I have no way. Now GRANDPA is breathing hard, and he keeps saying, "go to the hospital, take me to the hospital. ".

I'm so sorry. But how do I get there?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ginger's suicide note

My father and grandmother don't know about it yet.

They can't know. I don't want to get another one in here.

Postscript

On the night of February 2,2020, I met her at Ginger's house, and her grandfather was too sick to breathe.

18:28 we called an ambulance

At 19:43, an ambulance arrived and two male nurses wheeled GRANDPA downstairs on stretchers

Arrived at the fever clinic of Concord Hospital at 20:10 and was told to register. The day has been taken out, have to wait until after midnight to take the number to see a doctor on the cure

20:20 GRANDPA can't breathe, and the nurse helps hang the Oxygenation, which goes from 55% to 84% 

At 21:00, GRANDPA couldn't make it, and was told that he would have to wait for the midnight call, stay up all night in the emergency room, see the doctor tomorrow morning, bed unknown

At 21:24, after the calls to the various hotlines, the Kong Hon District government pushed the health hotline, and after the health hotline was pushed to the Community Secretary, the community secretary said, "I will react with the streets. I have no choice. My personal recommendation is that you stay in the hospital. "

At 21:50 a body was carried out from before us

At 22:00, GRANDPA snorted in his weak breath, "stop looking and go back to the house. I want to die. "

22:30 at 110, the community car was refused, we chose to give GRANDPA covered with a thick quilt, wheelchair home
